State: items (array) and page (number, starting at 1).

API: https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts?_page=${page}&_limit=10.

The Fetch: When the component mounts OR when page changes, fetch data.

The "Senior" Logic: Do not replace the items state. 

You must append the new data: setItems(prev => [...prev, ...newData]).

The Button: A button at the bottom that says "Load More" (disabled while loading).


********

Input: The hook should take a url as a string.

Output: The hook should return an object containing:

data: The fetched JSON.

isLoading: Boolean status.

error: Any error message.

refetch: A function to trigger the fetch again manually.

The Goal: Clean up your LoadMoreFeed component so it only handles UI, while the hook handles the Network.



